<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-80-0687 </DOCNO><TEXT>A control technology assessment of various methods to control worker exposureto asbestos during brake repair was reported for the Vehicle MaintenanceFacility at the U.S. Post Office Building in Louisville, Kentucky. Resultsindicated that effective control of asbestos dust was achieved with thesystem used; one of 22 samples had a detectable level. Recommendationsfor better work practices were presented.</TEXT></DOC>